            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In a 12-year-old Moroccan girl (patient 1) with hypomyelinating leukodystrophy and chondrodysplasia (HLD26; 620269), Guasto et al. (2022) identified homozygosity for a 3-bp in-frame deletion (c.1218_1220del, NM_178148.3) in exon 4 of the SLC35B2 gene, resulting in deletion of a highly conserved leucine residue at codon 407 (Leu407del) within the putative protein-transporter domain. Her unaffected first-cousin parents and 2 unaffected sisters were heterozygous for the deletion, which was not found in the dbSNP, ExAC, or gnomAD databases. RT-PCR of patient fibroblasts showed significantly reduced SLC35B2 mRNA compared to control fibroblasts. Immunofluorescence assay of transfected HEK293F cells showed that wildtype SLC35B2 colocalized with a marker specific to the Golgi apparatus, whereas the mutant protein showed partial mislocalization, with diffuse signal in the cell. The authors noted that this patient was also found to be homozygous for an R1062W substitution in the CUL7 gene (609577), a gene associated with 3-M syndrome (3M1; 273750).</Attribute>
